      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented test suite covering hemolysis model; all deviations logged and resolved prior to production runs.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM v9) is version-controlled and a regression test suite exists, but coverage of the custom hemolysis source-term implementation is incomplete. Only 6 of 18 planned unit tests for the NIH model were executed and documented. Achieved level 2 against required level 4 at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) or equivalent applied to all governing equation terms including hemolysis transport; convergence order confirmed.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was applied to the Navier-Stokes solver but not extended to the hemolysis scalar transport equation. Formal order-of-accuracy confirmation is absent for the hemolysis model. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation applied on at least three grid levels; GCI < 2.5% for primary QoI (NIH) at all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mesh independence study was conducted across three grid densities and GCI was computed. GCI < 2.5% achieved for NIH at all five VAD operating points. Temporal discretization error was not formally quantified; time-step sensitivity was assessed qualitatively only. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (fluid properties, pump geometry tolerances, measurement uncertainty) fully characterized and traceable to calibrated instruments.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements were performed using bovine blood with documented hematocrit (35±2%) and temperature (37±0.5°C). However, pump geometric tolerances and surface roughness of the test article were not reported, introducing unquantified geometric uncertainty. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., mean absolute error, validation uncertainty) computed and compared against pre-specified acceptance threshold; all operating points addressed.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute error of 8.3% computed against the 15% acceptance criterion across all five operating points. Validation uncertainty (experimental plus numerical) was estimated but not propagated through a formal ASME V&V 20 framework. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH) are identical to or demonstrably representative of the COU QoIs; mapping between validation and COU QoIs is documented.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary clinical hemolysis metric and is used directly in both validation and COU predictions. However, sub-lethal hemolysis markers (free plasma hemoglobin kinetics) relevant to chronic VAD use were not validated. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the same pump geometry and at COU operating conditions (flow rates, speeds); any extrapolation documented and justified.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic pump geometry, which approximates but is not identical to the target VAD device geometry. Operating conditions overlap partially (3 of 5 flow-speed points within validated range; 2 require extrapolation). Extrapolation uncertainty was not quantified. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
