      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selection justified against experimental data; sensitivity to model form alternatives quantified.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model were selected based on literature precedent but no formal model-form sensitivity study was conducted for the VAD geometry. Alternative hemolysis models (e.g., modified power-law, strain-based) were not evaluated. Factor not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (fluid properties, boundary conditions, hemolysis model constants) traceable to calibrated sources; uncertainty ranges assigned and propagated via Monte Carlo.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed over three primary inputs (inlet velocity, dynamic viscosity, hemolysis model constant C). Blood density and pump wall roughness were treated as deterministic without justification. Traceability of hemolysis model constant C to primary experimental data is incomplete. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
